cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically fine-grained classification, and proposes a new architecture for feature encoding using bilinear pooling and matrix normalization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses machine learning techniques such as matrix normalization and sub-matrix square-root layer, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel architecture, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of moments and matrix operations could also suggest that it belongs to cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the use of compact pooling methods, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
